The paper deals with object recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves incremental learning and updating of features, which is a key aspect of machine learning (cs.LG). The method also involves detecting instances from unknown classes, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve real-world datasets, which are often used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
